@page "/importexport"

@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms

<h1 class="import-export-title">Import / Export</h1>

<div class="import-export-container">
    <InputFile class="input-file" OnChange="ImportCsv" accept=".csv" />
    <div class="import-button-row">
        <button class="add-btn"
                @onclick="SubmitCsv"
                disabled="@(!importFinished || IsError)">
            Submit CSV
        </button>

        <button class="add-btn"
            @onclick="ExportResultCsv"
            disabled="@(!importFinished || !IsError)">
        Download result
        </button>
    </div>
    <button class="add-btn" @onclick="ExportCsv">
        Export CSV
    </button>
</div>

@if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(StatusMessage))
{
    <p class="@(IsError ? "status-error" : "status-success")">
        @StatusMessage
    </p>
}

<h1 class="mb-4">Import / Export Guide</h1>

<p>
    This page allows you to <strong>import</strong> and <strong>export</strong> your Pokémon collection.
</p>

<h2>Contents</h2>

<ul>
    <li><a href="importexport#explanation">Explanation</a></li>
    <li><a href="importexport#examples">Examples</a></li>
    <li><a href="importexport#accepted-values">Accepted Values</a></li>
</ul>

<p>
    The export feature can be used to:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Create a backup of your Pokémon collection.</li>
    <li>Transfer your Pokémon to another computer or browser.</li>
    <li>Edit or create large amounts of Pokémon at once.</li>
</ul>

<p>
    Pokémon are exported as a <strong>CSV (Comma Separated Values)</strong> file.
    This file can be opened as a text file and edit manually, or with applications such as <strong>Microsoft Excel</strong>,
    <strong>Google Sheets</strong>, <strong>LibreOffice Calc</strong>, or any other spreadsheet editor.
</p>

<p>
    After making your changes, simply save the file again as a CSV and import it back into the application.
</p>

<hr />

<h2 style="scroll-margin-top: 90px;" id="explanation">Explanation</h2>

<p>
    The CSV file must contain the following columns in this exact order and separated with commas:
</p>

<blockquote class="blockquote">
    <p>
        Id,Pokemon,Nickname,IsAlpha,HasHiddenAbility,Gender,Nature,HpIv,AttackIv,DefenseIv,SpAttackIv,SpDefenseIv,SpeedIv,Particles
    </p>
</blockquote>

<h3>Import Results</h3>

<p>
    After importing your CSV, if there are no errors, you will be able to submit your pokemons. If any rows contain errors, you can download a results CSV that identifies the rows that failed and explains why.
</p>

<h3>Column Reference</h3>
<p>
    Each column is described below, along with its requirements and expected values.
</p>

<div style="  margin-bottom: 20px;">
    <span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
    </span> : You must fill the column.
    </div>
    <div>
    <span style="background:#2BCCE3;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
        Optional
    </span> : You can leave it empty, but the column must be there.
    </div>

<h3>Id</h3>
<span style="background:#2BCCE3;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Optional
</span>
<p>
    The Pokémon identifier.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Leave it empty to create a new Pokémon.</li>
    <li>Keep the value if you exported the Pokémon and want to update it.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Pokemon</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    The Pokémon species.
    You can use the Pokémon name exactly as it appears in-game.
</p>

<h3>Nickname</h3>
<span style="background:#2BCCE3;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Optional
</span>
<p>
    Optional nickname used to help identify the Pokémon inside the application.
</p>

<h3>IsAlpha</h3>
<span style="background:#2BCCE3;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Optional
</span>
<p>
    Whether the Pokémon is an Alpha Pokémon.
    You can use either the text value (<strong>True</strong>/<strong>False</strong>)
    or the numeric value (<strong>1</strong>/<strong>0</strong>).
</p>

<h3>HasHiddenAbility</h3>
<span style="background:#2BCCE3;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Optional
</span>
<p>
    Whether the Pokémon has its Hidden Ability.
    You can use either the text value (<strong>True</strong>/<strong>False</strong>)
    or the numeric value (<strong>1</strong>/<strong>0</strong>).
</p>

<h3>Gender</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    The Pokémon's gender.
    You may use either the gender name or its numeric value.
</p>

<h3>Nature</h3>
<span style="background:#2BCCE3;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Optional
</span>
<p>
    The Pokémon's Nature.
    You may use either the Nature name or its numeric value.
</p>

<h3>HP IV</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    HP Individual Value.
    Valid values range from <strong>0</strong> to <strong>31</strong>.
</p>

<h3>Attack IV</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    Attack Individual Value.
    Valid values range from <strong>0</strong> to <strong>31</strong>.
</p>

<h3>Defense IV</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    Defense Individual Value.
    Valid values range from <strong>0</strong> to <strong>31</strong>.
</p>

<h3>SpAttack IV</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    Special Attack Individual Value.
    Valid values range from <strong>0</strong> to <strong>31</strong>.
</p>

<h3>SpDefense IV</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    Special Defense Individual Value.
    Valid values range from <strong>0</strong> to <strong>31</strong>.
</p>

<h3>Speed IV</h3>
<span style="background:#dc3545;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Required
</span>
<p>
    Speed Individual Value.
    Valid values range from <strong>0</strong> to <strong>31</strong>.
</p>

<h3>Particles</h3>
<span style="background:#2BCCE3;color:white;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.75rem;">
    Optional
</span>
<p>
    The particle effects attached to the Pokémon.
</p>

<p>
    Multiple particles can be assigned by separating them with a semicolon (<strong>;</strong>).
</p>

<p>
    You may use either the particle names or their numeric values.
</p>

<hr />

<h2 style="scroll-margin-top: 90px;" id="examples">Examples</h2>

<pre>
,Ditto,,False,False,Ditto,Bold,0,0,0,0,0,0,

,Beldum,,False,False,Genderless,,0,0,0,0,0,0,

,Bulbasaur,,False,False,Male,Jolly,26,5,31,25,14,9,ShinyPhantom;Phantom

This last example is equivalent to the one above, but uses numeric values instead of text:
,Bulbasaur,,0,0,0,11,26,5,31,25,14,9,0;1
</pre>

